@node copyright "Tab2Spc - Copyright and spreading"

  This program is FreeWare. It means that you can use it and spread it
  gratuitously. But I reserve the copyright to it.

  You mustn't charge any fee for spreading it. You are allowed to charge
  a fee for make a copy of a PD program of course.

        This program may be spreaded only with the following files:

                     Tab2Spc                - @{"main program" link description}
                     Tab2Spc_eng.guide      - English documentation
                     Tab2Spc_eng.guide.info - its icon
                     Tab2Spc_pol.guide      - Polish documentation
                     Tab2Spc_pol.guide.info - its icon

  This program may be also spreaded as an archive. I do not agree to
  spread it as a crunched file because there is nothing that you could
  compress besides the executable file. But the executable file should
  not be crunched because its so small that compression would not give
  much gain, and a file would not be able to make it @{"resident" link description 20}.

  The source code of this program is not spreading but you can get it from
  me.
@endnode

@node usage "Tab2Spc - What does it do?"

  Do you fashion many texts using a computer?

  If you do, so do you get nervous when words in the text are seperated
  with tabs, and not with spaces?

  Then if you set the text-cursor at the beginning of the word and you
  press the BACKSPACE key then the word merges with the previous one.

  It throws me out of balance, so I have written this simple program
  which converts the tab-codes into a space-codes.
@endnode

@node description "Tab2Spc - Program description"

  This program is very simple.

  I have wanted the program to be very short, so It can be started from
  the Shell only.

  You have to enter three arguments

  <tab size (1..8)> (source file> <destination file>

  the first one is the quantity of space-codes that composes the
  tabulator, the second and a third one are the source and destination file
  name. As the first argument I advise you to enter 8.

  Program would not create a destination file if the source file doesn't
  contain tabulators.

  When it finishes it writes the source and destination file length, and
  a number of found tabs.

  Because it works only as a Shell command I decided to add possibility
  to make it resident. It means that if you use the 'Resident' command
  you are able to place the program into resident programs list. It
  will then stay in memory until you reset the computer. If the program
  were compressed it could not be made resident. Anyway it is so
  short that compression would not give much gain...
@endnode

@node history "Tab2Spc - Program history"

  1.0  - First version. It had got two bugs which has been corrected in the
         next version. It had not possiplilty to define the tabulator size.

      1. When the quantity of characters before the word was the same as
         behind it then the word that was before tabulator and a word
         behind the tabulator have been merged in one.

      2. If the situation from the 1 point occured then additionally
         after merging the words in one zero has been added behind them.

  1.01 - The two bugs which were in the previous version of the program
         have been corrected.

  1.02 - I have added possibility to define the tabulator size.

  1.03 - This program has a very major bug its previous version. If the
         converted file had more than 8191 tabulators then Tab2Spc
         crashed. It happened because I used wrong multiply function.
         In this version the bug was corrected.

  1.04 - I have changed multiply function and the main converting function.
         Now it is faster and more reliable.
@endnode

